FEMI MAKINDE The Osun State  Commissioner for Women, Children and Social Affairs,  Olubukola Olaboopo and the Chief Whip of the state House of Assembly, Tunde Olatunji,  have made the list of top 100 most distinguished young African leaders. They were  conferred with the Royal African Youth Leadership Award by the Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi. The plaques were presented to them by the Minister for Youths and Sports, Mr Sunday Dare. This is contained in a statement on Saturday. Some of the other awardees are: Lateef Adedimeji, Kenny Blaq,  Oyo State House of Assembly Speaker, Debo Ogundoyin, the grandson of the late President Shehu Shagari, Bello Shagari, and the grandson of Nigeria’s foremost politician late Obafemi Awolowo; Seyi Awolowo. The commissioner urged the youths to start to think differently and ask themselves if as individuals, they are ready to take up leadership roles. While Speaking, the Ooni who is the chief host, hailed the awardees. The Ooni said, “Africa is  reaping a tremendous demographic dividend from this generation with exciting and fascinating growth which is altering the continent’s socio-economic development for good.” The minister stressed that if any government refused to invest on its youths such a government would witness a retrogressive development. He noted that 1.5 million Nigerian youths were targeted to be employed this year by the Federal Government and the Government is ready to partner with the Royal African Youth Leadership Forum. Copyright PUNCH.
